---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Product Strategy Impact — Lisa Wilkins"
  description="How Lisa Wilkins transformed complex product ecosystems into clear, scalable frameworks — streamlining delivery cycles by 43% for platforms serving 1.3M+ monthly users."
  ogImage="/og/strategy.png"
>
  <!-- Page header -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-slate)] pt-20 pb-16 px-6" aria-labelledby="page-heading">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-white opacity-70 mb-4">Strategy</p>
      <h1 id="page-heading" class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-extrabold text-white leading-tight mb-6 max-w-2xl">
        From complexity to clarity
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-white opacity-70 max-w-xl">
        Product Strategy · UX Architecture · Delivery Optimization
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Lead -->
  <section class="bg-white py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-charcoal)] leading-relaxed mb-6">
        I've made a career of stepping back, finding the signal, and building the simple, scalable structure underneath.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-[var(--color-dark-gray)] leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Whether inherited or fresh earth, I bring the same approach: distill the chaos into foundational components, align the competing requirements, and deliver a system that serves the product long after the launch.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-[var(--color-dark-gray)] leading-relaxed">
        I've built and inherited a platform serving 1.3M+ monthly users across web, mobile, and OTT with no unified content architecture. I distilled convoluted user journeys, organized content taxonomies, and broke down competing business requirements into foundational components — work that streamlined delivery cycles by 43% and extended well beyond any single release. The hardest, yet most rewarding, part of design is making things simple.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stats bar -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-slate)] py-10 px-6" aria-label="Key outcomes">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <div class="text-white text-center">
        <p class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold leading-none mb-2">43%</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest opacity-70">Faster delivery cycles</p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-white text-center">
        <p class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold leading-none mb-2">1.3M+</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest opacity-70">Monthly users</p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-white text-center col-span-2 md:col-span-1">
        <p class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold leading-none mb-2">10+</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest opacity-70">Years of leadership</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Test, learn, pivot -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-light-bg)] py-16 px-6" aria-labelledby="test-heading">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto max-w-2xl">
      <h2 id="test-heading" class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6 leading-tight">
        Test, learn, pivot
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-[var(--color-dark-gray)] leading-relaxed">
        At NBCUniversal and PragerU, I fostered team environments where critical thinking and candid feedback became expected. That foundation made usability testing, market analysis, and data-driven iteration more than process checkboxes; at PragerU, it's how I demonstrated the value of qualitative user testing to an executive team that was initially skeptical.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Unity -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-cream)] py-16 px-6" aria-labelledby="unity-heading">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto max-w-2xl">
      <h2 id="unity-heading" class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6 leading-tight">
        Unity nourishes your competitive advantage
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-[var(--color-dark-gray)] leading-relaxed">
        Early in my career, Sara Fortier's work on North Star Principals reshaped how I think about product leadership. Building a shared vision provides cross-functional partners a single point of alignment. When everyone is building toward the same outcome, collaboration stops being a process problem and becomes a competitive advantage.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main content area — to be filled with full case study -->
  <section class="bg-white py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[var(--color-mid-gray)] mb-6">Full case study</p>
      <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-[var(--color-dark-gray)] leading-relaxed">
        Additional case study content — process, artifacts, outcomes, and visuals — will be added here.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Back nav -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-light-bg)] py-10 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto flex items-center justify-between">
      <a href="/nbc-news" class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-mid-gray)] hover:text-[var(--color-coral)] transition-colors">
        &larr; NBC News
      </a>
      <a href="/connect" class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-mid-gray)] hover:text-[var(--color-coral)] transition-colors">
        Connect &rarr;
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
